Senator Daniel Inouye, a true American hero, has passed away. He served as a Senator for Hawaii for many years and was known for his work in strengthening the military, promoting bipartisan cooperation, and holding government officials accountable. Inouye's bravery during World War II, where he lost his arm but earned the Medal of Honor, earned him the respect and admiration of all who knew him. The thoughts and prayers of the nation are with the Inouye family during this difficult time.